.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
Attach to: Roll Button (Canvas > Background > Options Panel > Roll Button)\&. 

No GameManager needed\&. Completely self-contained\&.

.PP
Rolls 2 dice (each 1-6) giving a total of 2-12 moves\&. Shows a tumbling animation before settling on the final result\&. The Roll button is disabled after rolling and re-enabled when \fBPlayerTurnManager\fP advances to the next turn\&.

.PP
SETUP:
.IP "1." 4
Select "Roll Button" in the Hierarchy\&.
.IP "2." 4
Add Component → \fBDiceRollManager\fP\&.
.IP "3." 4
Create a small "Dice Panel" somewhere on the Canvas to display results: • Two Image GameObjects for the die faces (Die 1, Die 2)
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Optionally assign 6 die-face sprites (index 0 = face 1, index 5 = face 6)
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Or leave dieSprites empty: each Image needs a child TMP Text and numbers will be shown as text instead • One TextMeshProUGUI showing the total, e\&.g\&. "Moves: 9"
.PP

.IP "4." 4
Drag those objects into the slots below\&.
.IP "5." 4
Drag "End Turn Button" into the End Turn Button slot so this script knows when to re-enable rolling for the next turn\&.
.PP

.PP
NOTE: End Turn button click is shared between this script and \fBPlayerTurnManager\fP — both listen to the same button independently, so there is no conflict\&. 

